com.nokia.maps.map

Interface MapContainer

  • All Superinterfaces:
    MapObject

    public interface MapContainer
extends MapObject
    This interface is used to group MapObjects thus allowing operations on a whole group of objects without the need to iteratively visit each MapObject individually. It may be used for group operations such as changing the visibility.

    • Method Detail

      • addMapObject

        void addMapObject(MapObject object)
                  throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        This method adds the given MapObject to the MapContainer. The same MapObject may be added to different MapDisplay instances but not multiple times to the same MapDisplay. This restriction is enforced whenever a MapObject is added. If the MapObject is already associated in the current MapDisplay an exception is thrown.
        Parameters:
        object - MapObject to be added
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the MapObject to be added is already associated with the MapDisplay of the MapContainer.

      • removeMapObject

        void removeMapObject(MapObject object)
        This method removes the given MapObject from the MapContainer.
        Parameters:
        object - MapObject to be removed

      • removeAllMapObjects

        void removeAllMapObjects()
        This method removes all the MapObjects which are managed by the MapContainer.

      • getAllMapObjects

        MapObject[] getAllMapObjects()
        This method retrieves all MapObjects which are managed by the container.It is not guaranteed that modifications on the result is reflected properly in the MapContainer. Please use addMapObject(MapObject object) / removeMapObject(MapObject object) to modify the list.
        Returns:
        Array containing all MapObjects inside the container
